<entry stylesheet="matteroverdrive:info/styles/guide.css">
    <page class="padded-page">
        <title size="2" class="matter-text small-title">The $itemName</title>
        <text class="matter-text text-block">The $itemName serves as a container for [item name=pattern_drive]. Each storage houses 6 [item name=pattern_drive].
            It's the only way to store item patters and make them available to other machines trough the matter network.
            The [block name=replicator] for example, requires the $itemName to acquire patterns for replication. </text>
        <image width="64" height="64" src="guide/pattern_storage_small.png" style="float:left;margin-right:4px"></image>
        <image width="156" height="64" src="guide/pattern_storage_wide.png"></image>
    </page>
    <page class="padded-page">
        <title size="2" class="matter-text small-title">How to use</title>
        <text class="matter-text text-block">Connect the $itemName to a Matter Network using [block name=network_pipe] trough the back.
            Machines like the [block name=matter_analyzer] or [block name=replicator] will try to find the first available $itemName.
            The [block name=pattern_monitor] will show patterns stored in each [item name=pattern_drive] of the $itemName.</text>
        <image width="64" height="64" src="guide/pattern_storage_connection.png" style="float:left;margin-right:4px"></image>
        <image width="186" height="64" src="guide/matter_analyzer_wide.png"></image>
    </page>
    <page class="padded-page">
        <recipe style="text-align:center"></recipe>
    </page>
</entry>